In article <1993Feb20.124638.20830@husc15.harvard.edu> blom@husc15.harvard.edu writes:
>Does anyone know about any particular examples of the encoding of meaning into
>music?

How about:

Cowan, G. M., 1948, "Mazateco whistled speech." Language 24, 280-286.
Herzog, G., 1945, "Drum signaling in a West African tribe." Word 1, 217-238.

Both of which happen to be in:
Hymes, D. (ed), 1964, _Language in Culture & Society_

